Date of Birth: about 1784<br/>
Birthplace: East Marlborough, Virginia, USA<br/>
Excommunicated: December 3, 1832<br/>
Death: about 1836<br/>
<br/>
Born about 1784 at East Marlborough, Chester Co., Virginia, to William and Mary Beverly Gause.
Converted from the Shaker sect, he was baptized about the end of 1831.
Set apart as counselor to Joseph Smith March 8, 1832; sent on a mission Aug. 1, 1832. Excommunicated Dec. 3, 1832. Died about 1836.